theorem
Th28: ((((seq is  non-zero & seq is  convergent) & ( lim seq ) = ( 0 )) & seq is  non-increasing) implies (for n holds ( 0 ) < ( seq . n )))
proof
assume that
A1: seq is  non-zero
and
A2: (seq is  convergent & ( lim seq ) = ( 0 ))
and
A3: seq is  non-increasing
and
A4: (ex n st (not ( 0 ) < ( seq . n )));
consider n such that A5: (not ( 0 ) < ( seq . n )) by A4;
now
per cases  by A5;
suppose A6: ( seq . n ) < ( 0 );

then ( - ( 0 ) ) < ( - ( seq . n ) ) by XREAL_1:24;
then consider n1 being (Element of ( NAT )) such that A7: (for m holds (n1 <= m implies ( abs ( ( seq . m ) - ( 0 ) ) ) < ( - ( seq . n ) ))) by A2,SEQ_2:def 7;
A8: ( abs ( ( seq . ( n1 + n ) ) - ( 0 ) ) ) < ( - ( seq . n ) ) by A7,NAT_1:12;
A9: n <= ( n1 + n ) by NAT_1:12;
then ( seq . ( n1 + n ) ) < ( 0 ) by A3,A6,SEQM_3:8;
then ( - ( seq . ( n1 + n ) ) ) < ( - ( seq . n ) ) by A8,ABSVALUE:def 1;
then ( seq . n ) < ( seq . ( n1 + n ) ) by XREAL_1:24;
hence contradiction by A3,A9,SEQM_3:8;
end;
suppose ( seq . n ) = ( 0 );

